HEADWORD: Cruiser
<hw>Cruis"er</hw> <pr>(kr?"z?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or a
vessel that, cruises;</def> <specif>Specif.</specif>: <fld>(Nav.)</fld>
<def>A man-of-war less heavily armed and armored than a battle ship,
having great speed, and generally of from two thousand to twelve
thousand tons displacement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

